17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 342.22 of Title 74, unless there
20 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Oklahoma
22 Volunteer Firefighter Support Program".
23
24
HB2759 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 342.23 of Title 74, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. There is hereby created a grant program to support training
5 needs of volunteer firefighters in Oklahoma. The program shall
6 assist volunteer firefighters to receive up to ten (10) hours in
7 training a year from programs approved by the State Fire Marshall or
8 by the Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry's
9 Forestry Division.
10 B. The State Fire Marshall shall create an application system
11 for volunteer firefighters to apply for the grant assistance. The
12 State Fire Marshall may promulgate rules for the grant program.
13 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 342.24 of Title 74, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
17 for the State Fire Marshall to be designated the "Oklahoma
18 Volunteer Firefighter Support Revolving Fund". The fund shall be a
19 continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall
20 consist of all monies received by the State Fire Marshall from
21 appropriations, donations, grants, or other sources of funding
22 specifically designated for deposit to the Oklahoma Volunteer
23 Firefighter Support Revolving Fund. All monies accruing to the
24 credit of said fund are hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and
HB2759 HFLR Page 2
